.TH "blkdev_zone_mgmt" 9 "blkdev_zone_mgmt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blkdev_zone_mgmt \- Execute a zone management operation on a range of zones
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" blkdev_zone_mgmt
.BI "(struct block_device *bdev "  ","
.BI "enum req_opf op "  ","
.BI "sector_t sector "  ","
.BI "sector_t nr_sectors "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bdev" 12
Target block device
.IP "op" 12
Operation to be performed on the zones
.IP "sector" 12
Start sector of the first zone to operate on
.IP "nr_sectors" 12
Number of sectors, should be at least the length of one zone and
must be zone size aligned.
.IP "gfp_mask" 12
Memory allocation flags (for bio_alloc)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Perform the specified operation on the range of zones specified by
\fIsector\fP..\fIsector\fP+\fInr_sectors\fP. Specifying the entire disk sector range
is valid, but the specified range should not contain conventional zones.
The operation to execute on each zone can be a zone reset, open, close
or finish request.
